He said the shares were bought for other 'foundations' and then 'held for a certain time. He said MCC share purchases had been 'going on for some time' through Yakosa. Goldman Sachs, the US investment bank, acted as broker to the deals. The SFO is also investigating whether Mr Robert Maxwell or Mr Kevin Maxwell breached the Companies Act by failing to disclose the purchases of the shares by the Swiss trusts. The MCC purchases by Yakosa and Servex are the object of an investigation by the SFO into an alleged illegal scheme to support the MCC share price. 